    &lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;
  &lt;/math&gt; and &lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;
    &lt;mi&gt;B&lt;/mi&gt;
  &lt;/math&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;footnotes&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;sup class=&quot;footnote-number&quot; id=&quot;footnote-2&quot;&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;p&gt; A geometric mean is a type of average, which indicates the typical value of a set of numbers by using the product of their values as opposed to the arithmetic mean which relies on their sum (&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geometric_mean&quot;&gt;Wikipedia, 2017&lt;/a&gt;) &lt;a href=&quot;#footnote-ref-2&quot;&gt;&amp;#x2191;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</data>
